Preheat the oven to 200°C. Place the @Portobello Mushrooms{3} onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pop the baking tray onto the top shelf of the oven. Roast until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While the mushrooms cook, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}.

Roughly chop the @baby plum tomatoes{125} into very small pieces. Place in a #bowl{}, making sure you don't leave behind any of the delicious tomato juices. Add a drizzle of @olive oil{} and squeeze in the @sriracha sauce{1}. > Be careful it's hot, just add a little to start. Season with salt and pepper to taste and set to one side. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30} and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the onion. Cook until softened and lightly coloured, ~{5-6%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and @Mexican style spice mix{1} (don't add it all if you don't like too much heat!). Cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the beans, @water for the beans{150} and @vegetable stock powder{1} to the pan. Stir everything together and cook until the beans begin to break down, ~{5-6%minutes}.

After 5-6 mins, break up half of the beans with a #potato masher{} (or the back of a fork) and continue simmering until the beans have thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat and season with salt and pepper to taste. Place the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} onto the middle shelf of the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Just before you're ready to serve, thinly slice the mushrooms (take care, they're hot!) and add their roasting juices to the bean filling to add some extra flavour. Once everything is ready, pop the tortillas on a #plate{} and fill them with the lettuce and beans. Top with the roasted mushroom slices on top and spoon over the tomato salsa. Sprinkle over the cheese, roll up and enjoy!